                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                    Decorative designs: <locus target="#7v #14v #22r #32r #39v #46r #54r #64v #72v #77v #88v #99v #102r #107v #113v #114r" facs="008 015 022 032 040 046 054 065 073 078 089 100 102 108 114">folss. 7v, 14v, 22r, 32r, 39v, 46r, 54r, 64v, 72v, 77v, 88v, 99v, 102r, 107v, 113v, 114r, </locus> (a line of alternating red and black dots);
                    <locus target="#113v #126v" facs="114 127">113v, 126v, </locus> (haräg);
                    <locus target="#133r" facs="133">133r, </locus> (a line of full stops);
                    <locus target="#134r #137r #143v" facs="134 137 144">134r, 137r, 143v</locus> (multiple full stops)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="a1">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#113v #114r" facs="114">Fols. 113v, 114r</locus>: Concluding Prayer for the Book of Psalms, standard version
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e1">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#60r" facs="060">Fol. 60r</locus>: Two words of text (“Half (of the) psalms”) encircled in red and black lines mark the midpoint of the psalms
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e2">
                      <desc>
                      <locus target="#144r #144v" facs="144 145">Fols. 144r, 144v</locus>: scrawls and crude drawings
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e3">
                      <desc>
                      words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#32r #53v #104v #105r #129v" facs="032 054 105 130">folss. 32r, 53v, 104v, 105r, 129v, </locus>, etc.);
                      lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#8r" facs="008">8r, </locus>);
                      lines of text are written in the upper margin with a symbol ( ) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#31r" facs="031"> f. 31r, line 3</locus>), and in another case where the symbol (┬) is used (<locus target="#67v" facs="068">, line 3</locus>);
                      erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#98r" facs="098">98r, </locus>);
                      text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#66r #106r" facs="066 106">66r, 106r</locus>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e4">
                      <desc>
                      The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an
                      appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the
                      scribe reduces the font size at the end of lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (throughout). This scribe also will complete
                      the line of text above the end of the line (e.g., <locus target="#1v #2r #2v #4v" facs="002 003 005">fols. 1v, 2r, 2v, 4v</locus>)
                      </desc>
                      </item>

                    </list>
                  </additions>
